  "body": "In the discussions about Remix Desktop, the idea came up about expanding the workspace templates.  \r\n\r\n(there were developed  in conversation with Matteo)\r\n\r\nHere are some options: \r\n\r\nAdditional templates organized by profession:\r\n\r\n## Lawyer - simple contracts\r\n - escrow (maybe too complicated)\r\n - signing statement\r\n     - Agreement on IPFS party signs\r\n     - string: People names\r\n     - address\r\n     - Boolean\r\n\r\n- timestamp contract\r\n- Marriage contract\r\n\r\n## NGO\r\n**fund raising project: simple tip jar**\r\n- Upon receipt of funds, an event is fired for the msg.sender\r\n\r\n**Keeping track of volunteers time**\r\n- Master list of addresses\r\n- Volunteer checks in & checks out - addr is saved\r\n- Checkin & checkout with double signature - worker, manager\r\nOwner, manager, volunteer\r\n\r\n**sign a petition**\r\n- url of doc to sign\r\n- list of addresses\r\n- \r\n## Musician\r\n- Registry\r\n    - Title, link to song, author, address\r\n- gig contract - escrow contract \r\n\t- venue address, band address, approver address, gig name, gig completed\r\n\r\n## Other ways of organizing - more generic and not by profession - like\r\n#### Basic Registry\r\nname, item, address\r\n\r\n#### Collectives\r\naddresses, owner, list of addresses\r\n\r\nalso lets keep in mind adding something like this:\r\nhttps://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/2.x/api/payment\r\n",
